					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I can't think of one. All games i know of used a status bar, perhaps with portrait bling, representing the party of adventurers prior to FF1. I suppose this stems from the tabletop role playing tradition where the characters are purely imaginary based on your co-players' vocal description, or - even cruder - a short description in the handbook, which carried over to text based adventures, crawlers, and so on.</div>

					
