				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I actually think there's untapped potential in having the party at the front, looking up at the enemy at the back for a classic rpg fight. In dialogue, i'd be interested by their facial expressions, body language, etc. In battle, i'm more interested watching what the enemy does, what kind of threats its design hints at, if it's teletexting a special move to be made soon. I'm thinking a tennis court view would be perfect for this purpose. It also leaves more sprite bandwidth to make for exciting looking monsters and advanced boss fights. <br /><br />Of course, final fantasy is also enabling something of a power fantasy via its mode - watching incredible moves (in later games that allowed for it), the change of sprite from an adept to a hero class: fighter to paladin, a thief to an assassin, or what be it. The peasant turned hero dream.</div>

					
